      "writtenOn": "2020-01-10T20:07:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I know this is the case because if I run \"make js-test-debug\", set breakpoints at the first executable lines of both ignores-page-sk.js and ignores-page-sk_test.js and rerun the test suite, the debugger will break on ignores-page-sk.js first, followed by the test.\n\nAs to *why* this is the case, I\u0027m not entirely sure. But by looking at our Karma configuration, it seems like the code under test is loaded[1] via the karma-webpack[2] plugin[3]. My guess is that plugins (along with any code they pull in) are loaded before the tests execute, which would explain the observed behavior. But I don\u0027t quite understand how Karma, karma-config or webpack work, so unfortunately I can\u0027t give you a definitive answer at this time.\n\n[1] https://cs.corp.google.com/skia/buildbot/common-sk/karma.common.js?l\u003d121\n[2] https://cs.corp.google.com/skia/buildbot/common-sk/package.json?l\u003d19\n[3] https://github.com/webpack-contrib/karma-webpack",
